Description:
Two Bedroom Inner Urban Delight
In another clever development in the historic Foy and Gibson precinct of Collingwood, award winning architects, Elenberg Fraser, have provided a true urban sanctuary. Less than 4km from the CBD, and close to the best of Smith and Brunswick Streets bar, cafe and restaurant scene, Oxley Apartments offer an amenities rich lifestyle for residents, including a rooftop garden terrace, swimming pool and lush landscaped gardens.
Conveniently located on the second floor of the Tailor building, this modern apartment showcases a light washed open plan design, with warm timber flooring and an easy to personalise neutral interior. Featuring contemporary stone topped kitchen with stainless steel appliances, island bench/breakfast bar and plenty of storage space, living zone with split system air-conditioning, double glazed windows and slider out to a sheltered private balcony. Serviced by a sleek central bathroom including large walk-in shower and discreet euro laundry, two elegantly carpeted bedroom each provide mirrored BIRS. Secure undercover parking for one, plus a storage cage and easy access to public transport, complete an ideal inner city property.
Please note, this apartment is tenanted on a fixed term tenancy until 05/06/2020.
Insights: 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Modern Luxury Inside A Local Icon
With a captivating partnership between modern elegance and the timeless allure of Collingwood's industrial history, this exceptional apartment presents an ideal opportunity for first homebuyers and astute investors alike to enter the increasing popular inner northern property market. As part of the iconic Foy and Gibson Woollen Mills, the light-filled and generously proportioned interior comprises an east-facing open plan living and dining room with well-appointed galley kitchen (SS gas cookware, integrated dishwasher and glass splashback) and polished concrete floors that opens through wall-to-wall glass double doors onto the private terrace, master bedroom with BIRs, central bathroom with Euro laundry, reverse cycle heating/cooling, intercom entry and secure OSP with storage cage on title. Less than 50m from local institution Proud Mary coffee roasters, the apartment enjoys amazing access to Smith Street cafes, bars, restaurants, boutiques and trams, an innumerable amount of side-street favourites and is just a short stroll through Fitzroy Gardens to the CBD or MCG.

Freestanding Edwardian packed with potential

The home boasts three large bedrooms, central bathroom, functional kitchen with meals, living area, sunny backyard plus external laundry and 2nd WC. In an ideal location, just a short stroll to one of many cafes, bars and pubs, CBD transport, parklands, hospitals and to the sporting precinct of Melbourne. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Flooded with light due to a north oriented layout, this exquisite terrace provides a sanctuary for young families or professionals seeking a low maintenance lifestyle. The crisp white interiors are warmed by polished timber floors, while showcasing period detail and flowing out onto a private alfresco setting. It’s immersed in the thriving hub of Collingwood, close to cafes, bars and restaurants, yet creates a retreat of sublime peace and privacy.
Picture Postcard pretty
With its elegant fretwork, lacing and early Victorian façade, this utterly charming double-storey terrace home boasts renovated classic and contemporary spaces to deliver a character filled ready-to-enjoy lifestyle. Entering into this beautifully kept home, lights streams in from all sides, its rich period detail and decoration noticeable, as you step into the cosy lounge room, with decorative Gas OFP and built in shelving greeting you off the street. Beyond to the open plan dining/kitchen area, warmed with wooden floors, updated with contemporary tones of snow white, stainless steel and cool greys. Adjacent lies the homes stylish bathroom encased in dark sophisticated accents. The North facing courtyard is fully paved and private, a lovely spot to enjoy a sunny drink or decorate with pots and planters. Venture upstairs to the two spacious bedrooms both with built-in robes and district views over Collingwood's slate blue & heritage rooftops. The large master overlooks Hotham Street, bedroom two offers clever built in storage including a delightful window bench to enjoy the sun or read a book. Impressive features include stone bench tops, Ilve appliance's, solid timber floors and high ornate ceilings throughout, split-system heating and cooling, gas-coal fireplace plantation shutters, separate laundry. Within walking distance are Smith Street & its trams, Victoria Park train Station and handy direct route into the CBD via Wellington St. Colorful Collingwood continues to grow and remains one of very few value packed inner city postcodes, its proximity to amenity superb, its urban heritage intact. This beautiful and well-loved terrace will make a happy home for many years to come. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
Insights: 52 Hotham Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2019 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Circa 1869 shopfront versatility
Own a piece of history and revel in the outstanding versatility of this landmark circa 1869 "Barnards Buildings" double storey Victorian shopfront. At the heart of a lifestyle locale boasting Mixed Use Zoning the options for a stylish business or upscale inner-city residence are endless, STCA. Impressive in its versatility, this two bedroom home displaying grand dimensions and lofty ceilings features bright open plan living with a CaesarStone kitchen and a renovated cellar where bluestone walls line a second living that opens to a flexible study. A neat bathroom, gas heating and OSP for two plus excellent storage completes this potential packed property, that boasts the entertainment, transport and shopping of Smith Street, Gertrude Street, Brunswick Street, and CBD walking distance.

Description:
Style & finesse amid Collingwood's best
With Congress Wine and Espresso at its door, and mere paces from Smith St's exciting eateries and bars, this 1-bedroom apartment by Milieu provides the perfect balance of function and flair for a vibrant inner-city lifestyle. Flaunting funky elements of stainless-steel surfaces and concrete ceilings against on-trend Oak floors, the home maximises living space through its brilliant interior design. A spacious open plan domain and a sunlit balcony overlooks the Cambridge St Reserve, offering indoor-outdoor living enhanced by a sleek Smeg kitchen with abundant clever storage. Coddled in ducted heating and cooling, with fitted robes to the bedroom, and a chic bathroom with Euro laundry, the home is complete with basement storage and a communal bike storage area with handy repair centre.

Description:
SoJo, MoJo
This substantial 1890s DS residence offers exciting scope to restore and extend (STCA) on a deep block with a second frontage to Little Oxford Street. With a versatile floor plan comprising up to 5 bedrooms, two bathrooms and generous parking options. Here is a rare opportunity to create a splendid family home in the prestigious and highly sought after SoJo (South of Johnston St.) precinct. Surrounded by local side-street iconic institutions including SoJo and Proud Mary cafes while just a short stroll from Gertrude, Smith and Brunswick Streets cafes, bars, galleries, boutiques and artisan delights. Numerous transport options including trams to the CBD, Fitzroy Aquatic Centre, Royal Exhibition Building, Melbourne Museum and IMAX Cinema, or just walk everything is so close!

Description:
Live Large With Private Lift & Internal Garage
Launched by a direct drive-in garage and your own private lift, luxury comes standard in this stunning three bedroom residence rising with architect-designed confidence to every occasion. Live and entertain, work and play; you can do it all in the peaceful privacy of this sensational modern townhouse with multiple alfresco areas then step out in style to nearby Smith and Gertrude Streets. Secured in a boutique complex of five, this brilliant home is bursting with natural light and cutting-edge quality. The main entrance hallway reveals two bedrooms (BIRs; huge 2nd opening to light court) and brilliant bathroom then leads up to an outstanding living and dining zone with well-appointed Ilve kitchen including extendable table plus north-facing balcony. Completing a picture of perfection is the main bedroom suite with its own bathroom, WIR and a sun-drenched terrace. Also featuring heating/cooling, secure entrance, video intercom, great storage and laundry area, this state-of-the-art residence is set to capture your imagination in one of inner-Melbourne's most exciting lifestyle precincts.

Description:
Renovated freestanding Victorian: move in and enjoy!
This beautifully renovated and extended Victorian residence is an appealing home for a small family or professional couple in a wide quiet street. Set in an unrivalled location, close to Smith Street cafes and bars, schools (Zoned for Clifton Hill PS), Queens Parade, Victoria Park and tram routes. Filled with light and immaculately presented, it offers two double bedrooms (custom BIRs) and a large bathroom/laundry opening from an arched hallway; well-equipped kitchen open to a spacious high-ceilinged living/dining room, flowing through French doors to a brick-paved al fresco entertaining courtyard. Features of this well located home include polished timber floors, ducted heating/cooling, split-system air conditioning and ceiling fans.

Epitomising the inner-northern lifestyle, this delightful worker's cottage enjoys an enviable position just a short stroll to an abundance of popular side-street cafes and gastro pubs, artisanal boutiques and the trams, restaurants and nightlife of vibrant Smith Street. With a light-filled and neutrally-toned interior, the home boasts a large open plan kitchen with dining and adjacent living areas that opens onto the paved rear garden with manicured gardens beds and concealed storage shed. Description:
Warehouse Conversion with Superb Scope
This rare warehouse residence is one of a kind and promises superb scope for a creative transformation, located right in the heart of Collingwood.
The versatile floor plan as is comprises of a generous sized kitchen and dining area on the ground floor, seven bedrooms, two bathrooms, second utility area, dining room and lounge rooms.
Offering space, soaring ceilings, rustic brick and raw timber throughout, with sky lights adding an abundance of natural light. This property offers great foundations for a renovation or redesign (Commercial 1 Zoning).
Additional highlights include a fireplace, storage rooms and R.O.W access with the potential for off-street parking (STCA).
Set amongst the dynamic atmosphere of Collingwood's restaurants, cafes, shopping, and public transport, enjoy a convenient lifestyle with every amenity on your doorstep.
Without doubt this is an exceptional opportunity, one that will rarely be repeated and therefore an inspection is a must.

Description:
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSING 21ST SEPTEMBER @ 5.00PM (UNLESS SOLD PRIOR)
Authentic city-fringe sophistication at its finest, this visually striking, two bedroom loft-style warehouse conversion is absolutely flawless and requires zero maintenance. The perfect union of 21st Century designer flair and a genuine industrial context, this edgy home features two secure basement parking spaces and incredible storage in an outstanding location between the very best of Smith St, Brunswick St and Victoria St.
Commanding its own street frontage, the home reveals a beautifully appointed CaesarStone kitchen with a gas oven / cooktop and open-plan living. With eye-catching, towering ceilings, the home also presents an upstairs master bedroom retreat enriched by generous built-in robes and its own ensuite, whilst downstairs the second bedroom is equipped with mirrored robes and convenient to a second bathroom.
Importantly for such a vibrant location, the home also features two secure basement parking spaces, intercom entry and an enormous storage cage (close to four times the normal size), as well as split system heating / cooling, a European laundry and volumes of under-stair storage.
Immerse yourself in a lifestyle enriched by the very best of the inner-North East - Smith St's cafe scene and nightlife is easily walkable, Brunswick St is just around the corner and Victoria St is also within metres where you can find the best Vietnamese food outside of Vietnam. Incredibly well-serviced by city-bound trams, trains and plenty of buses, you are also just a leisurely stroll from the leafy parks of East Melbourne.
NELSON ALEXANDER PTY LTD

Description:
Designer Style with Light and Luxury
Complemented by its world-class residents' facilities and secure surrounds, this sixth-floor apartment presents an exceptional lifestyle/investment opportunity in the Elenberg Fraser-designed Oxley complex - all in one of Melbourne's most dynamic inner-city neighbourhoods. Stylish and sophisticated interior highlights one large bedroom with mirrored robes and deluxe bathroom with floor-to-ceiling tiles, open-design living/meals area enhanced by a stone-top kitchen with soft-close drawers, Ariston cooking appliances and integrated Ilve dishwasher. Along with an enclosed balcony flanked by floor-to-ceiling windows for an abundance of natural light, the apartment also includes split-system heating and cooling, concealed laundry facilities, double glazing, intercom, plus lift to secure entrance foyer, lower-level parking space and storage cage, residents' swimming pool and private garden. The best of Collingwood and Fitzroy at your fingertips, it's walking distance to Smith Street's boutique shops and major supermarkets, cool cafes and renowned restaurants, trams to hospital precincts and the CBD.

Description:
Must-live location - Collingwood
Strategically located right in the centre of Collingwood, the Yorkshire Brewery Apartments are only three kilometres North-East of Melbourne CBD. Surrounded by fantastic bars and restaurants, Melbourne's oldest shopping strip - Smith Street, factory outlets, public transport within walking distance and much more. It is truly a must-live destination!
This 2 bedroom apartment comes complete with good size bedrooms plus a study nook, well designed bathrooms, kitchen equipped with stainless steel appliances and European laundry. The features also including built-in-robes, dishwasher, split system heating and cooling, floor boards throughout the living and dining areas, NBN network connection, security entrance and intercoms.
Residents of Yorkshire Brewery also have exclusive access to the gymnasium, outdoor BBQ and sun tanning area, lounge and meeting room.
Please register your interest today for upcoming inspections!
